WorkCover Queensland have been providing workersâ€™ compensation insurance across Queensland for more than 20 years and are dedicated to supporting Queensland workers and businesses, from managing claims and rehabilitation, to injury prevention and ensuring employers have the right cover to protect their teams. As a government-owned but self-funded organisation, WorkCover Queenslandâ€™s commitment is to delivering fair, efficient and compassionate support, understanding that every worker and business is different, and keeping premiums low for employers while helping injured workers achieve the best possible return-to-work outcomes. With a vision to be the best workersâ€™ compensation insurer and make a positive difference to peopleâ€™s lives, WorkCover Queensland partner with and support their customers to keep Queenslanders working.

To enable this vision and support the delivery of the organisationâ€™s aspirations and strategic roadmap of project and transformation, WorkCover Queensland are seeking an experienced leader for the role of Head of Product and Actuarial. This role will be a key leader within the organisation, contributing to WorkCover Queenslandâ€™s ongoing transformation journey and measuring outcomes to sustain continued growth.

About the role

Reporting to the Chief Financial Officer, the Head of Product and Actuarial oversees four critical portfolios: pricing and compliance analytics, business insights and actuarial, premium support and strategy, and customer audit and intelligence.
Specifically, this role will:

Lead and develop a high-performing analytical and actuarial team, driving advanced modelling, projections and predictive analytics to optimise insurance risk and support pricing and valuation reviews.
Shape and oversee WorkCoverâ€™s product, pricing and actuarial functions, integrating financial, operational and data insights to inform strategic decisions and ensure fair, sustainable premiums.
Act as a trusted advisor to the CFO and Executive Leadership Team, providing expert guidance on actuarial strategy, operational challenges, and emerging risks to strengthen financial integrity and business performance.
Champion continuous improvement and innovation, enhancing data accuracy, pricing systems, reporting capability, and operational efficiency across product and actuarial processes.
Foster strong partnerships internally and externally including with the regulator, State Actuary, and key industry stakeholders to ensure clear, transparent communication of financial performance, compliance, and pricing outcomes.
Lead engagement on premium strategy, scheme sustainability, and policy reform to reinforce WorkCoverâ€™s leadership and reputation within the Queensland workersâ€™ compensation landscape.
Key to the success of this role will be the ability to innovate and bring a customer-focused mindset, communicate with influence, and apply a pragmatic and commercial lens to judgement and decision-making. This role will be empowered to create and drive solutions that enable long-term partnerships and align to WorkCover Queenslandâ€™s regulatory obligations and strategic direction.

About you

To be successful in this role, you will be a highly experienced, strategic actuarial and business leader with proven expertise in overseeing product and actuarial functions, ensuring compliance with regulatory frameworks, governance standards, and WorkCover Queenslandâ€™s operational objectives. You will possess deep knowledge of the financial services sector and a strong understanding of the commercial, regulatory, and socio-political factors influencing the organisation and its stakeholders. You will demonstrate exceptional analytical and actuarial capabilities, including developing and implementing statistical and predictive models, evaluating complex policy and legislative frameworks, and using data-driven insights to guide strategic decision-making.

A proven leader of high-performing, cross-functional teams, you excel in guiding senior executives through complex business transformations, capability enhancements, and operational improvements and have demonstrated experience in producing strategic position papers and influencing executive and Board-level stakeholders to align diverse perspectives, inform enterprise-wide strategy, and deliver sustainable, measurable business outcomes.

Tertiary qualifications in business, actuarial science or a related discipline complemented by postgraduate qualifications in actuarial studies and/or membership of the Institute of Actuaries (or equivalent) is essential for this role.

Future Generation Joint Venture (FGJV) is the principal contractor for Snowy Hydro's Snowy 2.0, Australia's largest committed renewable energy project. We bring the combined engineering expertise of three companies - Italy's Webuild (formerly Salini Impregilo), Australian-based Clough and US-based Lane Construction.

Snowy 2.0 is the next chapter in the Snowy Scheme's history. It is the largest committed renewable energy project in Australia and will provide on-demand energy and large-scale storage for many generations to come. This Iconic Project has and will continue to create its own legacy in Australian history.
